# Audit fix (A-2) — stop the Cursor IDE from surfacing AGENTS.md / SOUL.md /
# USER.md from inactive git worktrees as `always_applied_workspace_rules`.
#
# Each worktree under `.claude/worktrees/` carries its own copy of the
# proactive-agent skill files (SOUL.md / USER.md / AGENTS.md). The host
# IDE walks the entire workspace looking for rule files and injects every
# match — so the main agent ends up reading 3-5 conflicting identity /
# workflow declarations pointing at paths that don't exist in the active
# checkout. We had no `.cursorignore` before; this file scopes rule
# discovery (and search indexing) to the active working tree.

.claude/worktrees/**

# Defense-in-depth: never let `.git/**` leak into rules / indexing.
.git/**

# Build artifacts — also not interesting for rule discovery.
dist/**
dist-electron/**
release/**
node_modules/**

# Bundled language servers / large model assets are not source rules.
bundled-lsp/**
resources/embeddings/**